3
1 (j) Engaging in conduct that is prohibited under section 411h
2 or 411i of the Michigan penal code, 1931 PA 328, MCL 750.411h and
3 750.411i.
4 (k) Any of the following with the intent to cause the
5 petitioner mental distress or to exert control over the petitioner
6 with respect to an animal in which the petitioner has an ownership
7 interest:
8 (i) Injuring, killing, torturing, neglecting, or threatening to
9 injure, kill, torture, or neglect the animal. A restraining order
10 that enjoins conduct under this subparagraph does not prohibit the
11 lawful killing or other use of the animal as described in section
12 50(11) 50(12) of the Michigan penal code, 1931 PA 328, MCL 750.50.
13 (ii) Removing the animal from the petitioner's possession.
14 (iii) Retaining or obtaining possession of the animal.
15 (l) Any other specific act or conduct that imposes upon or
16 interferes with personal liberty or that causes a reasonable
17 apprehension of violence.
18 (2) If the respondent is a person who is issued a license to
19 carry a concealed weapon and is required to carry a weapon as a
20 condition of his or her employment, a police officer licensed or
21 certified by the Michigan commission on law enforcement standards
22 act, 1965 PA 203, MCL 28.601 to 28.615, a sheriff, a deputy sheriff
23 or a member of the Michigan department of state police, a local
24 corrections officer, a department of corrections employee, or a
25 federal law enforcement officer who carries a firearm during the
26 normal course of his or her employment, the petitioner shall notify
27 the court of the respondent's occupation before issuance of the
28 personal protection order. This subsection does not apply to a
29 petitioner who does not know the respondent's occupation.
